  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Luke 22:66-71",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 22:66-71",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And as soon as it was day, the elders of the people, and the chief-priests, &c., came together ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— When the band of soldiers arrived at the high-priest’s with Jesus, they found many of the chief-priests, and the scribes, and the elders assembled there. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 14:53",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) Some persons of distinction, however, may have been absent, whose coming the rest would wait for. Wherefore, although the soldiers brought Jesus to the high- priest’s a while after midnight, his trial did not begin till about three in the morning: the intermediate time being spent in procuring witnesses, in sending for the absent members, in gathering the clerks and officers of the court, and in fitting up an apartment for the trial. For, that Jesus was tried by the council, not in the temple, as many suppose, but in the high-priest’s palace, is evident from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where we are expressly told, that they led Jesus from Caiaphas’s house to the pretorium. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Saying, Art thou the Christ? tell us ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Dost thou give up the pretensions thou hast formerly made, or dost thou maintain them? If thou art indeed the Messiah, tell us plainly, and it will bring matters to a short issue. It seems, these wretches hoped to gain a great advantage against Jesus either way; if he confessed it, they would condemn him on that confession; and if he denied it, they would expose him on that denial, as afraid to maintain the pretensions he had made. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And he said, If I tell you ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That I am the Christ, and give you the most convincing proofs of it, you are resolved that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "you will not believe. And if I ask you ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— What you have to object against the proofs I produce; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "you will not answer me ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Here he seems to refer to their silence, when he put a question to them which would have led them to his own authority, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 20:5-7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Nor let me go ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— If I be not the Christ, you ought to answer the arguments by which I prove that I am; if I be, you ought to let me go; but you will do neither: you will only overbear me with renewed violence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Hereafter shall the Son of man sit, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — The day will come, when ye shall see the Son of man, who now stands in this despised and lowly form at your tribunal, exalted to all the dignity and glory which that high title imports; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sitting on the right hand of the power of God ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— And coming with irresistible strength to take vengeance on the proudest of his enemies. See on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:59-64",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 14:53-65",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Then said they all, Art thou then the Son of God? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— A number of them cried out together, feigning great astonishment at the blasphemy, as they were pleased to call it, of his answer, and desiring him to repeat it, lest they might have mistaken him, asked, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Art thou then the Son of God? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Both these, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Son of God, and the Son of man, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "were known titles of the Messiah, the one taken from his divine, and the other from his human, nature. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And he said unto them, Ye say that I am — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This, according to the Jewish manner of speaking, was a plain and strong affirmation of the thing expressed. When the high-priest heard our Lord’s second reply, he solemnly rent his clothes, crying out, that he had spoken blasphemy; and, appealing to the council, he said, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "What need we any further witness? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 22:71",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And they said, What need we, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — The council replied, As you have justly observed, what need have we of witnesses now, seeing we ourselves have heard in what manner he hath blasphemed? And being asked what punishment he deserved, they answered, that he deserved death. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:66",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "22:63-71 Those that condemned Jesus for a blasphemer, were the vilest blasphemers. He referred them to his second coming, for the full proof of his being the Christ, to their confusion, since they would not admit the proof of it to their conviction. He owns himself to be the Son of God, though he knew he should suffer for it. Upon this they ground his condemnation. Their eyes being blinded, they rush on. Let us meditate on this amazing transaction, and consider Him who endured such contradiction of sinners against himself.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
