  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And as soon as it was day,....  See Gill on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 27:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The elders of the people; or \"the presbytery of the people\", that were chosen from among the people to sit in the sanhedrim; the Israelites, as distinct from priests and Levites, and the doctors: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the chief priests and the Scribes came together; which made up the great sanhedrim, or council of the nation: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and led him into their council; or sanhedrim, the place where the sanhedrim sat, which was in the temple, and in the chamber called  , \"the paved stone chamber\" (n); here they usually met, and so the Persic version renders it, \"where their congregation was daily there\". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(n) Misna Saobedrin, c. 10. sect. 2. & Middot, c. 5. sect. 3.",
        "children": [
