  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "{21} And as soon as it was day, the elders of the people and the chief priests and the scribes came together, and led him into their council, saying,",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{21}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " And as soon as it was day, the elders of the people and the chief priests and the scribes came together, and led him into their council, saying,",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(21) Christ is wrongly condemned of blasphemy before the high priest's judgment seat in order that we might be acquitted before God from the blasphemy which we deserved.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Meyer's NT Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 22:66-67",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". According to Luke, the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Sanhedrim",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " now first comes together after daybreak, and Jesus is led in for trial. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Where",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " it assembled Luke does not say, and there is nothing therefore opposed to our finding in this place the leading away from the court of Annas (see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 22:54",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") into the house of Caiaphas (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The trial itself, as to its matter, is plainly the same which Matthew—although immediately after the bringing in of Jesus—makes to be held in the house of Caiaphas. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:59",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ff. Luke relates the matter and proceedings in a merely summary and imperfect manner.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὸ πρεσβυτέριον κ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "λ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the elders of the people",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", (the) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "chief priests, and scribes",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". These are the three constituent elements of the Sanhedrim. Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 9:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 20:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". On ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πρεσβυτέριον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", denoting the elders as a corporation, comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 22:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". By the non-repetition of the article the three parts are bound into a unity, in respect of which the difference of the gender and number is no difficulty (comp. Plato, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Pol",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". vi. p. 501 D: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τοῦ ὄντος τε καὶ ἀληθείας ἐραστάς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; Soph. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Oed. C",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". 850: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πατρίδα τε τὴν σὴν καὶ φίλους",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), especially in respect of the collective nature of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πρεσβυτέριον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". See in general, Krüger, § 58. 2. 1; Winer, p. 115 f. [E. T. 157 f.].",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀνήγαγον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The subject is the assembled members of the Sanhedrim who had ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "caused",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Him to be brought up. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀνα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " indicates a locality ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "situated higher",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as contrasted with the court of Annas, in which locality the Sanhedrim were met.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰς τὸ συνέδρ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἑαυτῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "into their own concessus",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", into their ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "own council gathering",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in order now ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "themselves",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to proceed further with Him. Comp. the use of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "συνέδριον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the Amphictyonic council, also of the Roman and the Carthaginian Senate (Polyb. xl. 6. 6, i. 11. 1, 31. 8).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
